OL,3,GNorth West
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA dry and bright start to the
OL,6,Fday. However, skies will quickly cloud
OL,7,Fover through the morning before patchy
OL,8,Frain and drizzle by late morning. Rain
OL,9,Fturns more persistent this afternoon.
OL,10,FFeeling chilly.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FRain, locally heavy, clears
OL,13,Faway east and broken cloud and showers
OL,14,Ffollow. The showers will be isolated,
OL,15,Fwith many places becoming dry.
OL,16,
OL,17,CSunday:FBright or sunny spells and
OL,18,Fisolated showers until mid to late
OL,19,Fafternoon, then the showers become
OL,20,Fmore widespread, frequent and often
OL,21,Fheavy, with a chance of thunder.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
